quiz questions in this lesson:

1.  What are descriptors?
    >> this is any class that declares the special methods __get__ and __set__
    >> this is any class that declares a special __get__ method
    >> is any class that declares the special methods __get__, __set__ and/or __del__

2.  How are descriptors conceptually different from property objects?
    >> one descriptor class can replace many similar property objects
    >> in one descriptor class, you can once describe the logic of interaction with internal
    (private or protected) variables

3.  What types of descriptors are there?
    >> non-data descriptor when the class has a __get__ method but no __set__ method
    >> data descriptor when __get__ and __set__ methods are present in the class
